Grey's Anatomy has updated it's reference manual to include two new medical conditions:  Pelosi and Biden.  Pelosi is actually an Italian derivative term for advanced dementia.  It's a combination of the words palsy and dropsy, which collectively describe the malfunctioning aspects of both the neurological and skeletal systems.  The Italian medical term is "cognitio communicato pelosi" which loosely translated means "unrecognized inability to communicate rationally and behave with coordination."  In the patient it presents with a slurring of speech, facial ticks and, often times, rambling speech and behavior.  It generally manifests itself in the elderly and predominantly affects women.  

Biden is actually Germanic in origin and comes from the German term "badenschadenfrueden".  The condition, similar to pelosi, generally manifests in the elderly but affects mainly men.  Hallmark symptomology is an inability to focus, squinting of the eyes, incoherence in speech, dry mouth syndrome, unsteadiness in both stance and gait, and periodic incontinence.  Patients afflicted with biden tend to also suffer from acute narcolepsy.  In more severe cases, patients suffer from bouts of delusion and paranoia, as well as "idiosympatic ideation of grandeur and cognitive disassociative persecution".  The classic example is a patient believing that he has engaged in physical combat with a person or persons when in reality they are figments of their imagination.  Patients also tend to, in more advanced stages, exhibit an aggressive nature challenging other men to fight them as if they were still high school rivals.

There is no cure for either pelosi or biden.  In both cases the prognosis is terminal in nature.  Most importantly, caretakers of individuals afflicted with these conditions are admonished to not allow these patients outside of their homes unattended.
